Direct Known Subclasses:
KmlContainer, KmlNetworkLink, KmlOverlay, KmlPlacemark, KmlTour
public class KmlFeature
extends KmlObject

The KmlFeature object is an abstract object and is the base for all feature types (for example Placemarks, Overlays, and NetworkLinks).

Nick

getBalloonHtml

public final java.lang.String getBalloonHtml()
Retrieves the contents of the feature's <ExtendedData> element. The retrieved contents are scrubbed to remove JavaScript; CSS; and iframe, embed, and object tags. It should be safe to insert the resulting HTML into your page without concern for malicious content embedded in the feature data; however any feature depending on CSS or Javascript will not work.

Returns:
the contents of the feature's <ExtendedData> element. The retrieved contents are scrubbed to remove JavaScript; CSS; and iframe, embed, and object tags. It should be safe to insert the resulting HTML into your page without concern for malicious content embedded in the feature data; however any feature depending on CSS or Javascript will not work.

getBalloonHtmlUnsafe

public final java.lang.String getBalloonHtmlUnsafe()
Retrieves the contents of the feature's <ExtendedData> element. The contents are not scrubbed. Use this method only if you trust the source of the feature data.

Returns:
the contents of the feature's <ExtendedData> element. The contents are not scrubbed. Use this method only if you trust the source of the feature data.

getVisibility

public final boolean getVisibility()
Returns:
True if the feature is drawn in the plugin. In order for a feature to be visible, the visibility of all its ancestors must also be set to true. In the Google Earth List View, each feature has a checkbox that allows the user to control visibility of the feature.

getComputedStyle

public final KmlStyle getComputedStyle()
Returns:
Returns the computed style of a feature, merging any inline styles with styles imported from setHref() or a StyleUrl. Note: Modifying the returned KmlStyle object is undefined and not recommended.

getOpacity

public final float getOpacity()
This is an experimental feature and can change (or even be removed) at any time. Retrieve the opacity of a feature, ranging from 0 (completely transparent) to 1 (complete opaque). The opacity of a folder or document will influence the opacity of child features. Thus, if a folder has an opacity of 0.5 and a child ground overlay in the folder also has an opacity of 0.5, the overlay will be drawn with an opacity of 0.25.

setOpacity

public final void setOpacity(float opacity)
this is an experimental feature and can change (or even be removed) at any time. Set the opacity of a feature, ranging from 0 (completely transparent) to 1 (complete opaque). The opacity of a folder or document will influence the opacity of child features. Thus, if a folder has an opacity of 0.5 and a child ground overlay in the folder also has an opacity of 0.5, the overlay will be drawn with an opacity of 0.25.

Parameters:
opacity - the opacity of a feature, ranging from 0 (completely transparent) to 1 (complete opaque). The opacity of a folder or document will influence the opacity of child features. Thus, if a folder has an opacity of 0.5 and a child ground overlay in the folder also has an opacity of 0.5, the overlay will be drawn with an opacity of 0.25.
